    <fn-group>
      <fn id="fn0010">
        <label>1</label>
        <p>It should be noted that this formalism is also applicable to resonances, where the pole in <mml:math id="M225" altimg="si15.gif" overflow="scroll"><mml:msub><mml:mi>&#x393;</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">[</mml:mo><mml:mn>2</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">]</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>k</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:math> is at a complex value of <mml:math id="M226" altimg="si16.gif" overflow="scroll"><mml:msup><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msup></mml:math> instead of a real value, which leads to a peak-structure for <mml:math id="M227" altimg="si17.gif" overflow="scroll"><mml:msup><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msup><mml:mo>&#x2208;</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="bold">R</mml:mi></mml:math>.</p>
      </fn>
    </fn-group>
